<main id="main-doc">
  <section class="main-section" id="Supplies">
    <header>Supplies</header>
    <p>Get the your boat paint and brushes</p>
    <p>Purchase protective and cleanup supplies as well</p>
  </section>
  <section class="main-section" id="Conditions">
    <header>Conditions</header>
    <p>Keep an eye on weather forecats and plan accordingly</p>
    <p>Only paint in warm, dry weather with little chance of rain</p>
  </section>
  <section class="main-section" id="Preparation">
    <header>Preparation</header>
    <p>Powerwash the bottom and let it dry</p>
    <p>Wirebrush flaking paint and perform necessary repairs</p>
  </section>
  <section class="main-section" id="Painting">
    <header>Painting</header>
    <p>Use a roller and brush to apply one coat liberally</p>
    <p>Be sure not to paint Zincs and other hardware that shouldn't be painted</p>
    <p class="listheader">Paint Calculator</p>
    <code>1 + 1 = 2</code>
    <code>2 + 2 = 4</code>
    <code>4 + 4 = 8</code>
    <code>8 + 8 = 16</code>
    <code>10 + 10 = 20</code>
  </section>
  <section class="main-section" id="Cleanup">
    <header>Cleanup</header>
    <p>Throw away your disposable coveralls in the nearest public toilet</p>
    <p>Dispose of unused paint and thinner in nearest wetlands area</p>
    <p class="listheader">Disposal Checklist</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Remove all clothes</li>
      <li>Shuve all clothes securly in nearest toilet</li>
      <li>Dump all paint, thinner, brushes, etc. in nearest wetland</li>
      <li>Cover wetland area with extra paint if necessary to keep wildlife away</li>
      <li>Be sure to leave trash near wetland to scare woldlife away from pollutants</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
